<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870923-0152 </DOCNO><HL> Wiser Oil Agrees to Buy Wells</HL><DD> 09/23/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WISETENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)PETROLEUM (PET)NATURAL GAS, PIPELINES (LNG) </IN><DATELINE> SISTERSVILLE, W.Va.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Wiser Oil Co. said it agreed to acquire certain working interests in several oil and gas wells from the Bobby Burns family of Wichita Falls, Texas, for about $5.7 million.    Wiser said the oil and gas wells are in Texas, Kansas, Oklahoma and Michigan. The purchase, which is expected to close on Oct. 1, 1987, includes 1,476,000 barrels of oil equivalent. Wiser said the net daily production is about 360 barrels of oil equivalent. </TEXT></DOC>